This paper deals with communication networks and channel state information, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses distributed state information and cooperation, which are relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of encoders and decoders, which are related to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses sufficient conditions, which are relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
